    }

Java 10 added direct support for `Charset` to the API, meaning there&#39;s no need to catch UnsupportedEncodingException:

    String result = java.net.URLDecoder.decode(url, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);

Note that a *character encoding* (such as UTF-8 or ASCII) is what determines the mapping of characters to raw bytes. For a good intro to character encodings, see [this article][1].


